Photo by Business | Motivation | Quote on August 08, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Bashar J Katou @basharjkatou #1- Choosing the Wrong Business Model I put over 200k in a restaurant business that didn't produce profits until it burned down-| couldn't even afford insurance for it and so lost everything in that fire I put 5k in Amazon and made millions with it- huge difference'.

Photo by Business | Motivation | Quote on August 08, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Basha J Katou @basharjkatou #2- Being Cheap I didn't want to spend money, so I paid my employees the minimum Because of that they were not loyal to me and couldn't care less when I lost everything. They were even threatening me to beat me up up if I didn't pay them the salary they still were owerd right after everything burned down'.

Photo by Business | Motivation | Quote on August 08, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of 1 person and text that says 'Bashar J Katou @basharjkatou #3- Being Stubborn When I finally was ready to start a new business, I was too proud and stubborn to realize sucked as a business owner. I refused to pay a coach, mentor or consultant for advice and lost several thousands of dollars to that ignorance'.

Photo by Business | Motivation | Quote on August 08, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Bashar J Katou @basharjkatou #4- Having a Scarcity Mindset I was taught that everyone is out to get me and I need to protect my money. I thought everyone is trying to scam me and that fear stopped me from growing as a person. If everyone is out to get me, who could I ask for help, who could I hire, how would I charge customers a fair price?'.

Photo by Business | Motivation | Quote on August 08, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of 1 person and text that says 'Bashar J Katou @basharjkatou #5- Flexing As soon as I made my first big money, I bought a Bentley Luckily, soon realized flexing isn't who I am and sold it after a few months. Still was a huge waste of money'.

Photo by Business | Motivation | Quote on August 08, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Bashar Bashar J Katou @basharjkatou #6- Thinking KH Having the Cheapest Prices is Good If your only selling point is being cheap, anyone can put you out of business by being cheaper. Selling cheap means you can't deliver quality and only quality creates a lasting business'.

Photo shared by Business | Motivation | Quote on August 08, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou. May be an image of text that says 'Bashar J Katou @basharjkatou If you want to start your business, don't make the mistakes I made. Do it right from the get-go. If you want to build a business your customers will love to pay you for, follow my page for more tips! (@basharjkatou)'.
